{"id":14880910,"mediaExerciseId":"a66bba91-d91b-46d2-a664-5a51b9fd5884","exerciseName":"12","chapterName":"5","chapterTitle":"Introduction to Valuation:The Time Value of Money","groupId":612293,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":148,"solutions":[{"id":6065732,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we have a set of fifty silver dollars from 1952 and we want to calculate the value of these coins for the time we retire.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"We know the following data:\n\n|Silver Coins||\n|--|--|\nFace value in 1952\t|$50\nAnnual appreciation rate|4.30%\nRetirement year| 2067","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"To calculate the Future Value (FV) of the coins for the year 2067 when we plan to retire, we are going to use the FV formula. \n\n$$ FV = PV\\cdot (1+r)^t$$\n\n*Where:*\n- PV is the future value\n- r is the applied rate\n- t is the periods of time the rate is applied\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"The first is to calculate the time (t) we need to take into account to apply our appreciation rate. \n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\nt & = 2067 -1952\\\\\n& = \\boxed{115}\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"Now we need to compute the formula with the given data to obtain the FV of the coins.\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\nFV &=\\$50 \\cdot (1+0.043)^{115} \\\\\n\\\\\n& = \\boxed{\\$6,333.82}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThe present value of the liability is of **$6,333.82** million.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"$6,333.82","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":true,"stepNumber":6}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"0ed25fe4-e422-467a-8434-ce3219b971fc","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":6}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14880911,"exerciseName":"13","page":148,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"e42dc2b1-11f2-4e23-8f89-b804b0fb46b6","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-5-questions-and-problems-13-e42dc2b1-11f2-4e23-8f89-b804b0fb46b6"},{"id":14880912,"exerciseName":"14","page":148,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"dee3d7c8-45c3-4dc8-8ecb-8d827dd03562","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-5-questions-and-problems-14-dee3d7c8-45c3-4dc8-8ecb-8d827dd03562"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14880909,"exerciseName":"11","page":148,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"2cfbfa68-f899-4ea7-8efa-54ee33dab024","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-5-questions-and-problems-11-2c